Mt Elgon leaders and residents have welcomed the appointment of Bungoma Deputy Governor Hillary Chongwony as the county&rsquo;s Jubilee Party secretary general.Led by former councillor James Shabatayi, the leaders on Wednesday said Chongwony has what it takes to move Jubilee&rsquo;s agenda forward.Chongwony will work with Governor Kenneth Lusaka, the Jubilee point man in Western, and Sirisia MP John Waluke, to popularise the party in the region considered an opposition stronghold.&lsquo;&rsquo;We are appealing to all Mt Elgon leaders and residents to join Jubilee Party, because it will form the next government,&rsquo;&rsquo; Shabatayi said.He urged residents to register as voters.JP supporter Michael Ndiwa urged residents to carry out peaceful campaigns. &ldquo;Let us be careful when picking leaders. Choos people who will not neglect our region,&rdquo; he said.